        "custom_text_if6npT": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Fit Is the Foundation of Confidence",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "h2",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 18,
            "text_lh": 0,
            "text_fw": 500,
            "text_ls": 1.5,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
            "hidden_mobile": false,
            "text_fs_mb": 16,
            "text_lh_mb": 21,
            "text_ls_mb": 1.5,
            "text_mgb_mobile": 10
          }
        },
        "custom_text_HkitE9": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "The foundation of confidence in any bikini is fit. Even the most beautifully designed bikini will feel uncomfortable if it does not sit correctly on the body. Fit affects how secure a bikini feels, how it moves with you, and whether you can relax while wearing it rather than constantly checking or adjusting it.\n<br><br>\nA well fitting bikini should sit smoothly against the skin without digging in, gaping, or shifting as you move. <a href=\"/collections/bikini-tops\" title=\"Luxury bikini tops\">Bikini tops</a> should feel supportive without relying on excessive padding, while <a href=\"/collections/bikini-bottoms\" title=\"Luxury bikini bottoms\">bikini bottoms</a> should stay in place without creating pressure points around the waist or hips. These details may seem small, but they have a major impact on how confident you feel throughout the day.\n<br><br>\nMany issues people associate with discomfort or self consciousness in swimwear are actually caused by poor construction. Weak elastic, inconsistent sizing, and fabrics that lose shape when wet can make a bikini feel unpredictable and uncomfortable. When fit is treated as a priority during the design process, these problems are largely eliminated.\n<br><br>\nWhen a bikini fits properly, you stop thinking about it. You are not adjusting straps or checking coverage. That freedom allows confidence to feel natural rather than something you have to work at.",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "p",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 16,
            "text_lh": 24,
            "text_fw": 300,
            "text_ls": 0,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
