        "custom_text_xqmBtd": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Choosing the Right Cut for Your Body and Your Comfort",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "h2",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 18,
            "text_lh": 0,
            "text_fw": 500,
            "text_ls": 1.5,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
            "hidden_mobile": false,
            "text_fs_mb": 16,
            "text_lh_mb": 21,
            "text_ls_mb": 1.5,
            "text_mgb_mobile": 10
          }
        },
        "custom_text_UzNPhE": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "The cut of a bikini plays a major role in how confident it feels to wear. Different silhouettes change how a bikini sits on the body, how much support it offers, and how comfortable it feels throughout the day. Confidence comes from choosing a cut that works with your body and your preferences, not from forcing yourself into a style that does not feel natural.\n<br><br>\nSome bikini tops offer more structure through shaping and coverage, while others feel lighter and more minimal. The same applies to bikini bottoms. <a href=\"/collections/high-waisted-bikinis\" title=\"High waisted bikinis\">Higher rise cuts</a> can create a feeling of support and security through the waist, while lower rise styles often feel more relaxed and effortless. Neither option is better than the other. The key difference is how they make you feel once you are wearing them.\n<br><br>\nCertain styles, such as <a href=\"/collections/bandeau-bikinis\" title=\"Bandeau bikinis\">bandeau bikinis</a>, suit those who prefer clean lines and a more streamlined look. When designed well, bandeau styles can feel surprisingly secure while offering a balanced, understated silhouette that many find confidence boosting.\n<br><br>\nIt is also important to consider how a bikini cut performs when you move. Sitting, walking, swimming, and spending long periods in the sun all affect how a bikini feels on the body. A cut that looks good standing still but shifts or feels restrictive during movement can quickly undermine confidence.\n<br><br>\nTaking the time to understand which cuts you feel most comfortable in allows you to choose bikinis that feel intuitive to wear. When the silhouette aligns with your comfort level, confidence feels natural rather than something you have to think about.",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "p",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 16,
            "text_lh": 24,
            "text_fw": 300,
            "text_ls": 0,
