            "text": "Why Fabric And Construction Make A Big Difference",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "h2",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 18,
            "text_lh": 0,
            "text_fw": 500,
            "text_ls": 1.5,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
            "hidden_mobile": false,
            "text_fs_mb": 16,
            "text_lh_mb": 21,
            "text_ls_mb": 1.5,
            "text_mgb_mobile": 10
          }
        },
        "custom_text_6ixJww": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Fabric and construction play a much bigger role in swimwear confidence than most people realise. A bikini can look beautiful at first glance, but if the fabric lacks structure or the construction is weak, that confidence quickly fades once it is worn for more than a few minutes. How a bikini feels against the skin, how it responds to movement, and how it holds its shape throughout the day all come back to these details.\n<br><br>\nHigh quality swimwear fabrics are designed to offer gentle support without feeling restrictive. They provide a level of hold that smooths and supports the body rather than clinging or sagging. Fabric weight also matters. Lightweight fabrics can feel comfortable initially but often lose their shape when wet, while more considered fabrics maintain structure and consistency throughout wear.\n<br><br>\nConstruction is just as important as fabric choice. Reinforced seams, secure elastic, and thoughtful lining placement all contribute to how stable a bikini feels once it is on. These elements prevent common issues such as rolling edges, shifting panels, or loss of support after swimming. When construction is done well, the bikini feels reliable rather than unpredictable.\n<br><br>\nConfidence comes from knowing that a bikini will behave the same way throughout the day as it did when you first put it on. When fabric and construction are treated as priorities rather than cost cutting opportunities, the result is swimwear that feels dependable, comfortable, and easy to wear.\n<br><br>\nA bikini that holds its shape, supports the body, and feels consistent over time allows you to focus on enjoying where you are, rather than thinking about what you are wearing.",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "p",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 16,
            "text_lh": 24,
            "text_fw": 300,
            "text_ls": 0,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
            "hidden_mobile": false,
            "text_fs_mb": 16,
            "text_lh_mb": 24,
            "text_ls_mb": 0,
            "text_mgb_mobile": 10
          }
        }
      },
