        "custom_text_MRbLgc": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Support Should Feel Built In, Not Overdone",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "h2",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 18,
            "text_lh": 0,
            "text_fw": 500,
            "text_ls": 1.5,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
            "hidden_mobile": false,
            "text_fs_mb": 16,
            "text_lh_mb": 21,
            "text_ls_mb": 1.5,
            "text_mgb_mobile": 10
          }
        },
        "custom_text_qypGTy": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Support is one of the most important factors in how confident a bikini feels to wear, but it is often misunderstood. Good support should feel integrated into the design rather than obvious or heavy. When a bikini is doing its job properly, you should feel held and secure without being constantly aware of structure or reinforcement.\n<br><br>\nBikini tops, in particular, rely on thoughtful design to provide support without compromising comfort. This can come from internal shaping, well placed lining, or fabric tension rather than padding alone. When support is built into the construction, the bikini feels balanced and comfortable instead of bulky or restrictive.\n<br><br>\nPoor support often shows itself through constant adjustments. Slipping straps, shifting fabric, or a lack of stability can make even a well styled bikini feel distracting to wear. These issues tend to pull attention away from how you feel and place it back on how the bikini is behaving.\n<br><br>\nWell designed support allows you to move naturally. Swimming, walking, sitting, and stretching should not change how secure the bikini feels on the body. When support is handled correctly, confidence comes from trust. You trust that the bikini will stay in place and feel consistent throughout the day.\n<br><br>\nSupport should enhance how a bikini feels, not dominate it. When it is subtle, reliable, and thoughtfully integrated, it becomes one of the strongest contributors to confidence in swimwear.",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "p",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 16,
            "text_lh": 24,
            "text_fw": 300,
            "text_ls": 0,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
            "hidden_mobile": false,
            "text_fs_mb": 16,
            "text_lh_mb": 24,
            "text_ls_mb": 0,
            "text_mgb_mobile": 10
          }
        }
      },
