        "custom_text_JqHXPa": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "Coverage, Comfort, and Wearing a Bikini in Real Life",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "h2",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 18,
            "text_lh": 0,
            "text_fw": 500,
            "text_ls": 1.5,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
            "hidden_mobile": false,
            "text_fs_mb": 16,
            "text_lh_mb": 21,
            "text_ls_mb": 1.5,
            "text_mgb_mobile": 10
          }
        },
        "custom_text_gKf99G": {
          "type": "custom_text",
          "settings": {
            "text": "It is easy to assume that more coverage automatically leads to more confidence, but that is not always the case. Confidence in a bikini comes from feeling comfortable and supported, not from how much skin is covered. A well designed bikini with less coverage can feel far more confidence boosting than a more covered style that shifts, digs in, or feels restrictive.\n\nConfidence is also shaped by how a bikini performs in real situations. Standing in front of a mirror is one thing, but wearing a bikini throughout the day places different demands on fit and construction. Sitting by the pool, walking along the beach, swimming, and spending hours in warm conditions all affect how a bikini feels on the body.\n<br><br>\nA bikini that feels comfortable at first but becomes distracting after movement or time in the sun can quickly undermine confidence. Fabric that overheats, elastic that tightens, or cuts that shift with movement draw attention back to the garment rather than allowing you to feel relaxed while wearing it.\n<br><br>\nWhen coverage and comfort are balanced correctly, the bikini becomes easy to wear. You are not thinking about how it looks when you sit down or whether it will stay in place when you move. Instead, confidence comes from trust. You trust that the bikini will feel the same at the end of the day as it did when you first put it on.\n<br><br>\nChoosing a bikini with real life wear in mind allows confidence to extend beyond appearance. When a bikini supports the body, moves naturally, and feels consistent throughout the day, confidence becomes a natural response rather than something you have to think about.",
            "remove_br_tag": false,
            "tag": "p",
            "fontf": "inherit",
            "text_cl": "#000000",
            "text_fs": 16,
            "text_lh": 24,
            "text_fw": 300,
            "text_ls": 0,
            "font_italic": false,
            "text_shadow": false,
            "text_mgb": 15,
            "hidden_mobile": false,
            "text_fs_mb": 16,
            "text_lh_mb": 24,
